<DOC><DOCNO> AP880518-0200 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-18-88 2033EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Gorbachev     05-18 0157</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Gorbachev,0162</SECOND><HEAD>Washington Post, Newsweek Editors Interview Gorbachev</HEAD><DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Editors from The Washington Post and Newsweekinterviewed Soviet leader Mikhail S. Gorbachev on Wednesday.   The Soviet news agency Tass reported that the interview tookplace, and the evening television news program ``Vremya'' showed ashort film clip of Gorbachev meeting the U.S. journalists.   Tass said the group included Washington Post Chairman KatharineGraham; Newsweek Editor Richard Smith; and Washington Post editorsJimmie Hoagland, Meg Greenfield and Robert Kaiser.   No details of the interview were released, but the Soviet mediasaid it would be published in the Soviet press on Monday followingits publication in Sunday's editions of the Post and next week'sissues of Newsweek.   Gorbachev granted the interview less than two weeks beforePresident Reagan arrives in Moscow for his fourth meeting with theSoviet leader.   Prior to traveling to Washington for their meeting in December,Gorbachev granted an interview to NBC News.</TEXT></DOC>